        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 12:11AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1211 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Taylorsville, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Taylorsville, Hickory, St. Stephens, Bethlehem, Stony Point, Love
Valley, Lake Hickory, Hudson, Granite Falls, and Conover.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
